How about (secure?) OO version (with no error handling)?<p><pre><code>  $c=new ReflectionClass('co');$m=$c->getMethod($_GET['m']);if($m && $m->isPublic()){$i = $c->newInstance();$m->invoke($i);}
</code></pre>
Example usage:<p><pre><code>  <?php
  // "Framework"
  $c=new ReflectionClass('co');$m=$c->getMethod($_GET['m']);if($m && $m->isPublic()){$i = $c->newInstance();$m->invoke($i);}

  // Controller
  class co 
  {
  	public function index()
  	{
  	    echo "index!";
  	}

  	public function test()
  	{
	    echo "yes, it's test.";  
  	}
  }

  ?>
</code></pre>
Call:<p>example.com/?m=index
example.com/?m=test
